{"id": "EUVD-2022-55714", "enisaUuid": "45af2414-eda3-3fc1-a314-7c0404cabfa9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nplatform/chrome: cros_ec_typec: zero out stale pointers\n\n`cros_typec_get_switch_handles` allocates four pointers when obtaining\ntype-c switch handles. These pointers are all freed if failing to obtain\nany of them; therefore, pointers in `port` become stale. The stale\npointers eventually cause use-after-free or double free in later code\npaths. Zeroing out all pointer fields after freeing to eliminate these\nstale pointers.", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T03:31:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T03:31:09", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0ceadb5a3e45f1b81cf54bd496b40a5e50b6bd40", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b610758bb3e0674644c1255cdafc2f46b7e05ff9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6613f36a2fa5c69e528bccba8b3d831f759dad2f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9a8aadcf0b459c1257b9477fd6402e1d5952ae07", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50642"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50642"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0bc97d19-29c1-3ddb-b4bf-68efd23f2671", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "1da9a288-3477-3f6b-ad99-fb18f1d5c9b8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f28adb41dab4a2795fd959750df57adffd2bb0be <9a8aadcf0b459c1257b9477fd6402e1d5952ae07"}, {"id": "2a98db4c-8480-3eff-b4bd-ff6a664550cf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f28adb41dab4a2795fd959750df57adffd2bb0be <b610758bb3e0674644c1255cdafc2f46b7e05ff9"}, {"id": "40bba1e4-e868-3b72-91bf-2200d2b14a20", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "f28adb41dab4a2795fd959750df57adffd2bb0be <6613f36a2fa5c69e528bccba8b3d831f759dad2f"}, {"id": "75ea4487-7cad-3a58-8d6f-963e7ddac3fb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.9"}, {"id": "97bcac7d-13e1-3eac-b7f6-4329f4f78eac", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_